		<div class="comment-content" style="display:block;">

			<p>It is possible in this country to work hard and become well-off if you do not give up. It is not incredibly possible because jobs are hard to come by and it is hard to find well paying jobs even with a college degree;however, it is still possible to find a job and make money. I think it is becoming harder now to work hard and become well-off because of the lack of jobs but also the lack of motivation a lot of people have.<br />
I still believe that America is the &#8220;land of opportunity&#8221; and that the American dream is alive. America is still a place to come for freedom and rights and opportunity to become someone. You can still work hard even if you do not become rich you can say you lived life well. The American dream is alive in my opinion because we are still able to work. I might not become rich over night or own my own company but the ability to do so is there and with it so is the American dream.<br />
Young people with wealthy families do have a large advantage because going to college and having credentials for jobs comes easier to them. Their parents have the money to send them to college and maybe come out with no debut, which a lot of people can not do, and then they have connections through their parents so yes it is easier for young people with wealthy families but it is not impossible to get a lot out of life for anyone.<br />
I am very optimistic about finding a job in the future because even if there are very few jobs in the world there are still jobs and I plan on trying my hardest to get one of those jobs. I might not live comfortably for a while but the key is to not loose hope and to not give up. I think living comfortably and having a job is something that is very possible with a lot of effort and a lot of faith.</p>

